<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,984,1644]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,984,1009]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Description.</emphasis>
Body length: 
<quantity box="[533,666,984,1009]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="12.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="10.0">10–15 mm</quantity>
; setae uniformly black, but mixed golden and black on legs; antennomeres uniformly black, III ca. twice as long as IV, XI slightly more than twice as long as wide (
<figureCitation box="[1331,1399,1021,1046]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="20.[151,250,824,846]" captionTargetBox="[177,1405,199,800]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[172,1414,193,803]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 8. Mylabris (M.) barezensis Serri, Pan &amp; Bologna: A. antenna; B. elytral pattern; C. mesosternum; D. tegmen, ventral view; E. tegmen, lateral view; F. aedeagus, lateral view; G. variation of the spiculum gastrale, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm. (from Serri et al., 2012)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286149/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Fig. 
<number box="[1385,1399,1022,1046]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
A); pronotum without fore transverse depression; elytral pattern (
<figureCitation box="[869,939,1059,1084]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="20.[151,250,824,846]" captionTargetBox="[177,1405,199,800]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[172,1414,193,803]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 8. Mylabris (M.) barezensis Serri, Pan &amp; Bologna: A. antenna; B. elytral pattern; C. mesosternum; D. tegmen, ventral view; E. tegmen, lateral view; F. aedeagus, lateral view; G. variation of the spiculum gastrale, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm. (from Serri et al., 2012)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286149/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Fig. 
<number box="[926,939,1060,1084]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
B) characterized by reduced yellow-brown surface and large extension of black colouration everywhere; mesosternum as in 
<figureCitation box="[1051,1116,1096,1121]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="20.[151,250,824,846]" captionTargetBox="[177,1405,199,800]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[172,1414,193,803]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 8. Mylabris (M.) barezensis Serri, Pan &amp; Bologna: A. antenna; B. elytral pattern; C. mesosternum; D. tegmen, ventral view; E. tegmen, lateral view; F. aedeagus, lateral view; G. variation of the spiculum gastrale, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm. (from Serri et al., 2012)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286149/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Fig. 
<number box="[1102,1116,1097,1121]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
C; male gonoforceps slender in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[327,393,1133,1158]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="20.[151,250,824,846]" captionTargetBox="[177,1405,199,800]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[172,1414,193,803]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 8. Mylabris (M.) barezensis Serri, Pan &amp; Bologna: A. antenna; B. elytral pattern; C. mesosternum; D. tegmen, ventral view; E. tegmen, lateral view; F. aedeagus, lateral view; G. variation of the spiculum gastrale, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm. (from Serri et al., 2012)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286149/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Fig. 
<number box="[380,393,1134,1158]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
E), and fused ventrally until the apical third (
<figureCitation box="[899,965,1133,1158]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="20.[151,250,824,846]" captionTargetBox="[177,1405,199,800]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[172,1414,193,803]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 8. Mylabris (M.) barezensis Serri, Pan &amp; Bologna: A. antenna; B. elytral pattern; C. mesosternum; D. tegmen, ventral view; E. tegmen, lateral view; F. aedeagus, lateral view; G. variation of the spiculum gastrale, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm. (from Serri et al., 2012)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286149/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Fig. 
<number box="[951,965,1134,1158]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
D); distal hook of aedeagus positioned far from apex, proximal hook slightly longer than the distal one, endophallic hook evidently curved (
<figureCitation box="[1289,1359,1171,1196]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="20.[151,250,824,846]" captionTargetBox="[177,1405,199,800]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[172,1414,193,803]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 8. Mylabris (M.) barezensis Serri, Pan &amp; Bologna: A. antenna; B. elytral pattern; C. mesosternum; D. tegmen, ventral view; E. tegmen, lateral view; F. aedeagus, lateral view; G. variation of the spiculum gastrale, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm. (from Serri et al., 2012)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286149/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Fig. 
<number box="[1345,1359,1172,1196]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
F); the apodeme of the 
<emphasis box="[349,555,1208,1233]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">spiculum gastrale</emphasis>
variable: most males have this sclerite slender in the middle and clearly narrowed and elongate in the last portion (
<figureCitation box="[625,690,1245,1270]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="20.[151,250,824,846]" captionTargetBox="[177,1405,199,800]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[172,1414,193,803]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 8. Mylabris (M.) barezensis Serri, Pan &amp; Bologna: A. antenna; B. elytral pattern; C. mesosternum; D. tegmen, ventral view; E. tegmen, lateral view; F. aedeagus, lateral view; G. variation of the spiculum gastrale, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm. (from Serri et al., 2012)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286149/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Fig. 
<number box="[677,690,1246,1270]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
Ga), but in a single male it is widened medially (
<figureCitation box="[1237,1303,1245,1270]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="20.[151,250,824,846]" captionTargetBox="[177,1405,199,800]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[172,1414,193,803]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 8. Mylabris (M.) barezensis Serri, Pan &amp; Bologna: A. antenna; B. elytral pattern; C. mesosternum; D. tegmen, ventral view; E. tegmen, lateral view; F. aedeagus, lateral view; G. variation of the spiculum gastrale, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm. (from Serri et al., 2012)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286149/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Fig. 
<number box="[1290,1303,1245,1270]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
Gb).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,984,1644]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,449,1283,1308]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Taxonomic remarks.</emphasis>
Immediately distinguishable from all species of the subgenus by the unique elytral pattern characterized by reduced brown-orange surface and the large extension of black colouration everywhere as in 
<figureCitation box="[180,246,1357,1382]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="20.[151,250,824,846]" captionTargetBox="[177,1405,199,800]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[172,1414,193,803]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 8. Mylabris (M.) barezensis Serri, Pan &amp; Bologna: A. antenna; B. elytral pattern; C. mesosternum; D. tegmen, ventral view; E. tegmen, lateral view; F. aedeagus, lateral view; G. variation of the spiculum gastrale, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm. (from Serri et al., 2012)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286149/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Fig. 
<number box="[232,246,1358,1382]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
B. Mesosternum (
<figureCitation box="[447,512,1357,1382]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="20.[151,250,824,846]" captionTargetBox="[177,1405,199,800]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[172,1414,193,803]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 8. Mylabris (M.) barezensis Serri, Pan &amp; Bologna: A. antenna; B. elytral pattern; C. mesosternum; D. tegmen, ventral view; E. tegmen, lateral view; F. aedeagus, lateral view; G. variation of the spiculum gastrale, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm. (from Serri et al., 2012)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286149/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Fig. 
<number box="[499,512,1358,1382]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
C) narrowed posteriorly and the setae on its anteriorly modified section are longer than usual. Male gonoforceps slender in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[752,819,1395,1420]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="20.[151,250,824,846]" captionTargetBox="[177,1405,199,800]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[172,1414,193,803]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 8. Mylabris (M.) barezensis Serri, Pan &amp; Bologna: A. antenna; B. elytral pattern; C. mesosternum; D. tegmen, ventral view; E. tegmen, lateral view; F. aedeagus, lateral view; G. variation of the spiculum gastrale, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm. (from Serri et al., 2012)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286149/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Fig. 
<number box="[805,819,1396,1420]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
E).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,984,1644]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
This species was included in the nominate subgenus by 
<bibRefCitation box="[853,1065,1432,1457]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refString="Serri, S., Pan, Z. &amp; Bologna, M. A. (2012) A new Mylabris species from south-eastern Iran and a key to the Iranian species of the nominate subgenus (Coleoptera, Meloidae). ZooKeys, 219, 81 - 86. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 219.3674" type="journal article">
Serri 
<emphasis box="[918,970,1432,1457]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[996,1058,1433,1457]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="2012.0">2012</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. It is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1775" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" box="[1255,1436,1433,1456]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Mylabris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apiceguttata">
<emphasis box="[1255,1436,1433,1456]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">M. apiceguttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of the shape of the ventral blade of claws and the aedeagal distal hook, far from apex. As discussed for 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1775" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Mylabris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apiceguttata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">M. apiceguttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, possible affinities with 
<taxonomicName box="[567,692,1507,1532]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Calydabris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[567,692,1507,1532]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Calydabris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are represented by the presence of a tuft of setae on the scutum of mesosternum, never pointed out in the literature. In conclusion, we tentatively include this species into the nominate subgenus but we are waiting for molecular evidences to support its phylogenetic position.
</paragraph>
